=== sw-cor24-rpg-ii Minimal RPG-II Demo (Chain Field-2 Third Shape) ===
Program:
H  control header
F  input file INFIL
I  field 01: A0110  (10-char input slice)
I  field 02: A0510  (6-char mid-record slice)
C  REVR01 -> calc stage 0
C  MOVE02 -> calc stage 1 reselects field 02
O  DETAIL01 output (10 chars)
O  DETAIL02 output (3 chars)
O  DETAIL03 output (6 chars)

Current boundary:
- Real today: stage 0 can still drive the third output-shape selection while
  calc slot 1 replaces the visible result with a different decoded field.
- This variant uses field 02 as a 6-byte slice, so DETAIL03 emits RD 01A-
  style prefixes instead of the field-01 prefix used by earlier 6-byte demos.

Current runtime-produced output:
RD 01A
RD 02B
RD 03C

Authored source: rpg2.hlasm
Tiny demo source: tiny_rpg_demo_chain_move2f6_6.src
Generated source: build/rpg2.generated.s
